'''''Stonkers''''' is a [[strategy video game]] for the [[ZX Spectrum]] published by [[Imagine Software]] in 1983. It was written by John Gibson with graphics by Paul Lindale. In 2013, ''TechRadar'' called it an early example of a [[real-time strategy]] game.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.techradar.com/news/gaming/loved-command-and-conquer-you-ll-love-these-ios-games-1124172|title = Loved Command and Conquer? You'll love these iOS games|date = 12 January 2013}}</ref>

==Gameplay==
''Stonkers'' is controlled either using keyboard or [[joystick]]. In the game, the player controls [[infantry]], [[artillery]], [[tank]], and supply-truck units.  Combat units consume supplies over time and the player must use the supply units to replenish them.  Supply units are unloaded while a ship docks at the player's port. Information about ongoing events is displayed in a ticker tape on the bottom of the screen.

==Reception==
It was awarded the title "Best Wargame" by ''[[CRASH (magazine)|CRASH]]'' in 1984.<ref>[http://www.crashonline.org.uk/12/awards.htm CRASH Issue 12], Readers Awards</ref>

